#Lyrics
O perfect life of love! All, all is finished now, All that He left His throne above To do for us below. No work is left undone Of all the Father willed; His toil, His sorrows, one by one, The Scripture has fulfilled.  2. No pain that we can share But He has felt its smart; All forms of human grief and care Have pierced that tender heart. And on His thorn-crowned head And on His sinless soul, Our sins in all their guilt were laid That He might make us whole.  3. In perfect love He dies; For me He dies, for me! O all-atoning Sacrifice, I cling by faith to Thee! In every time of need, Before the judgment-throne, Thy work, O Lamb of God, I'll plead, Thy merits, not mine own.  4. Yet work, O Lord, in me As Thou for me hast wrought; And let my love the answer be To grace Thy love has brought. I cannot work my soul to save, That work is done by Thee; But I would work as one forgiven, Who rests his hope in Thee.  5. Then all eternity Low at Thy feet I'll lay My crown of life, and there for aye My grateful homage pay. "Not unto us," my heart doth sing, "But unto Thee be glory, King!" O Savior, all the praise to Thee For love so great, so free!

